Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Police have launched a manhunt for a group of about 10 men who opened fire on mourners at a night vigil in the Tembehlihle informal settlement in Lenasia on Friday evening.Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said on Saturday that two men were killed during the shooting.Dlamini said eight other people were wounded and taken to hospital.Saaberie Chishty paramedics were dispatched to the scene at 23:35 on Friday night where they found a chaotic scene, with several people scattered on the ground.The motive for the shooting was still unknown.Dlamini said no arrests had been made.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.